records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kenneth J Lux in court, in custody, with attorney Katherine Graber.   Stephen Joseph Centinario appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Graber makes statements.  Court conducts plea colloquy.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  State makes sentencing recommendations.  Defense makes sentencing recommendation.  Defendant makes statements.  The Defendant was given the following:
Count 1:

WITHHELD SENTENCE; (Credit time 77 days, if revoked)

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEARS;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

CONDITION TIME: 30-days HUBER, the last 28-days are STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  
Defendant is to be released on 12-23-17.

Attorney Graber requests expungement.  Court denies.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
